{"lemma":"دافِقٌ","slug":"دافِقٌ","root":"د.ف.ق","root_slug":"د-ف-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ف-ق","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دافِق","root":"دفق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12750"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%90%D9%82%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of دَفَقَ (dafaqa⁩).","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"bursting forth in a flood (of water, tears, etc)","examples":[{"text":"خُلِقَ مِن مَّآءٍۢ دَافِقٍۢ","english":"˹They were˺ created from a spurting fluid"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb دَفَقَ (dafaqa⁩)."},"ipa":["/daː.fiq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12750","headword_ar":"دَافِقٌ","root":"dfq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaqahu","text_ar":"دَفَقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pouring forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAfiqu xayorK","text_ar":"دَافِقُ خَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[May it be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring forth good"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said in prognostication on the occasion of the pouring forth of the contents of such a thing as a mug. (Lth, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N daAfiqN","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ دَافِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madofuwqN","text_ar":"مَدْفُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water poured forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (IKoot, S, Msb, K;) because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaqa","text_ar":"دَفَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is trans. [only] accord. to the generality (K, TA) of the leading lexicologists; (TA;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sir~N kaAtimo","text_ar":"سِرٌّ كَاتِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makotuwmN","text_ar":"مَكْتُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKoot, S, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArifN","text_ar":"عَارِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwfN","text_ar":"مَعْرُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaASimN","text_ar":"عَاصِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoSuwmN","text_ar":"مَعْصُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKoot, Msb,) after a manner obtaining among the people of El-Hijáz, who change the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEil","text_ar":"فَاعِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"when it is used as an epithet: (Fr, Msb, TA:) or it means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw dafoqK","text_ar":"ذُو دَفْقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a pouring forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (Mgh, Msb, TA;) accord. to Kh and Sb (TA) and Zj; (Msb, TA;) and in like manner they say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sir~N kaAtimN","text_ar":"سِرٌّ كَاتِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw kitomaAnK","text_ar":"ذُو كِتْمَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to Lth, [i. e.] in the 'Eyn, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water pouring forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out, at once:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) it occurs in the Kur lxxxvi. 6; where"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAfiq","text_ar":"دَافِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said by Kh and Sb to signify"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munodafiq","text_ar":"مُنْدَفِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Az, TA:) and it [there] means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sperma genitale."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","IKoot","S","Msb","Fr","Az"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}